 the goal is posterior-chain loading."],"quality_gate":["Pain-free range of motion.","Kettlebell path stays controlled.","Posture remains organized under load.","Athlete can stop the set before grip or alignment fails."],"stop_signs":["Sharp pain or joint pinching.","Grip becomes unsafe or bell path becomes uncontrolled.","Spine, shoulder, hip, knee, ankle, or wrist position cannot be maintained.","Breath-holding, dizziness, or pressure symptoms dominate the set."]}'::jsonb,
  pairing_logic = '{"pairs_well_before":["Posterior-chain accessory","Loaded carry","Restore / cooldown"],"pairs_well_after":["Ankle mobility","Bodyweight squat patterning","Glute activation"],"good_for_sessions":["squat_prep","strength_accessory"],"avoid_before":[],"avoid_after":[],"do_not_use_when":["The athlete cannot control the kettlebell safely.","Pain appears in the loaded pattern.","Grip or posture fails before the target tissues are trained.","The session needs true max-speed or jump Output and this would create fatigue first."]}'::jsonb,
