  coaching_execution = '{"movement_description":"Double Kettlebell Strict Press trains high-demand bilateral overhead strength with strong trunk and rack organization using kettlebell resistance. The athlete organizes the body first, creates tension through the handle and floor, moves through a range they own, and stops the set before technique breaks.","setup":["Clean or assist the kettlebell into the starting position without turning the setup into a conditioning rep.","Stack ribs over pelvis, squeeze the handle, and set the shoulder before pressing or curling.","Use a stance or kneeling base that lets the athlete control the bell without leaning."],"execution_steps":["Lower the kettlebell with control until the target stop point is reached.","Keep wrist, elbow, shoulder, ribs, and pelvis organized at the bottom.","Press with strong intent while keeping the rest of the body quiet and stable.","Finish the rep under control, reset the breath and shoulder, then repeat."],"coach_cues":["Own the start before the rep starts.","Strong, controlled, repeatable.","Brace, then move the bell.","Stack wrist over elbow; press from a packed shoulder.","Ribs down as the bell moves."],"athlete_cues":["Strong and clean beats heavy and sloppy.","Stop before the bell controls you.","Make the last rep look like the first rep."],"breathing_cues":["Inhale to prepare and brace before the hard part.","Exhale through the effort without losing trunk position.","Do not use long breath holds with youth, beginners, older adults, or pregnancy/postpartum athletes."],"common_faults":["Chasing load after position quality breaks.","Turning the set into a rushed conditioning station instead of strength work.","Pressing with rib flare, neck tension, or wrist collapse.","Losing shoulder position at the bottom or overhead finish."],"quality_gate":["Pain-free range of motion.","Kettlebell path stays controlled.","Posture remains organized under load.","Athlete can stop the set before grip or alignment fails."],"stop_signs":["Sharp pain or joint pinching.","Grip becomes unsafe or bell path becomes uncontrolled.","Spine, shoulder, hip, knee, ankle, or wrist position cannot be maintained.","Breath-holding, dizziness, or pressure symptoms dominate the set."]}'::jsonb,
