  coaching_execution = '{"movement_description":"Kettlebell Bottoms-Up Curl trains curl strength with high wrist, grip, and shoulder-control demand using kettlebell resistance. The athlete organizes the body first, creates tension through the handle and floor, moves through a range they own, and stops the set before technique breaks.","setup":["Clean or assist the kettlebell into the starting position without turning the setup into a conditioning rep.","Stack ribs over pelvis, squeeze the handle, and set the shoulder before pressing or curling.","Use a stance or kneeling base that lets the athlete control the bell without leaning."],"execution_steps":["Curl the kettlebell without swinging the torso or letting the shoulder roll forward.","Keep the wrist quiet and the elbow path consistent.","Lower with control until the arm is ready to repeat cleanly.","Stop before grip failure turns the rep into a swing."],"coach_cues":["Own the start before the rep starts.","Strong, controlled, repeatable.","Brace, then move the bell.","Pull elbow toward hip; shoulder blade back and down.","Quiet torso, strong grip."],"athlete_cues":["Strong and clean beats heavy and sloppy.","Stop before the bell controls you.","Make the last rep look like the first rep."],"breathing_cues":["Inhale to prepare and brace before the hard part.","Exhale through the effort without losing trunk position.","Do not use long breath holds with youth, beginners, older adults, or pregnancy/postpartum athletes."],"common_faults":["Chasing load after position quality breaks.","Turning the set into a rushed conditioning station instead of strength work.","Shrugging instead of pulling with the upper back.","Twisting the trunk to create range instead of rowing with control."],"quality_gate":["Pain-free range of motion.","Kettlebell path stays controlled.","Posture remains organized under load.","Athlete can stop the set before grip or alignment fails."],"stop_signs":["Sharp pain or joint pinching.","Grip becomes unsafe or bell path becomes uncontrolled.","Spine, shoulder, hip, knee, ankle, or wrist position cannot be maintained.","Breath-holding, dizziness, or pressure symptoms dominate the set."]}'::jsonb,
